comment:
* This class represents an XPath boolean object, and is capable of
 * converting the boolean to other types, such as a string.
 * @xsl.usage advanced

variables.name: S_TRUE
variables.comment:
* A true boolean object so we don't have to keep creating them.
   * @xsl.usage internal

variables.name: S_FALSE
variables.comment:
* A true boolean object so we don't have to keep creating them.
   * @xsl.usage internal

methods.name: public int getType()
methods.comment:
* Tell that this is a CLASS_BOOLEAN.
   *
   * @return type of CLASS_BOOLEAN

methods.name: public String getTypeString()
methods.comment:
* Given a request type, return the equivalent string.
   * For diagnostic purposes.
   *
   * @return type string "#BOOLEAN"

methods.name: public double num()
methods.comment:
* Cast result object to a number.
   *
   * @return numeric value of the object value

methods.name: public boolean bool()
methods.comment:
* Cast result object to a boolean.
   *
   * @return The object value as a boolean

methods.name: public String str()
methods.comment:
* Cast result object to a string.
   *
   * @return The object's value as a string

methods.name: public Object object()
methods.comment:
* Return a java object that's closest to the representation
   * that should be handed to an extension.
   *
   * @return The object's value as a java object

methods.name: public boolean equals(XObject obj2)
methods.comment:
* Tell if two objects are functionally equal.
   *
   * @param obj2 Object to compare to this  
   *
   * @return True if the two objects are equal
   *
   * @throws javax.xml.transform.TransformerException
